commit.message:
provide a pkg-config crossguid.pc file

pkg-config makes it easy for consumers of this library to obtain the
required CFLAGS and LDFLAGS. cmake makes it easy to fill the required
variables and install it along with the devel files.

Signed-off-by: Olaf Hering <olaf@aepfle.de>

make crossguid a real library by providing a proper SONAME

Extend the existing set_target_properties() to set also VERSION and SONAME.

Signed-off-by: Olaf Hering <olaf@aepfle.de>

Select the required C++ standard

Building crossguid requires c++17 since commit d9e6cd1d489062772f72b829e12cb354d804cffe
gcc7 includes support for this standard, and gcc7 is generally available since a long time.

Fixes #47

Signed-off-by: Olaf Hering <olaf@aepfle.de>
eval MATRIX_EVAL

Newer compilers only
Upgrde gcc version used by travis

commit.message:
Add delete permissions to the include files

Currently the install files are copied with permissions that do not allow a normal user to delete them. This causes a problem when the code is cloned and built in a folder as part of a nightly build. We are unable to remove the folder ready for the next night without using sudo.
Would you consider accepting my change as other people might benefit from it.

Add delete permissions to the include files

Currently the install files are copied with permissions that do not allow a normal user to delete them. This causes a problem when the code is cloned and built in a folder as part of a nightly build. We are unable to remove the folder ready for the next night without using sudo.
Would you consider accepting my change as other people might benefit from it.
